    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large upper-level floor spaces directly below the roof of commercial buildings or warehouses, originally unpartitioned but often modified for secondary use; may also be used for domestic sleeping or storage platforms set close to ceilings or roofs and open to and overlooking a living space below. For enclosed spaces under sloping roofs, between the roof and the ceiling of the uppermost story, especially in houses, use "attics (interior spaces)." For substantial interior spaces at the level of an upper story, usually extending the full length or width of rooms, use "galleries (upper level spaces)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dakverdiepingen van gebouwen, die als woning zijn ingericht. Gebruik 'penthouses' voor luxe appartementen op dakverdiepingen. Gebruik 'zolders' voor afgesloten ruimten onder schuine daken, tussen het dak en het plafond van de bovenste verdieping, vooral in huizen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>商用建築物或倉庫屋頂正下方的大型上層樓面空間，原先未經分隔，但也可能因另作他用而改裝。亦指鄰近天花板或屋頂，俯瞰下層起居空間的開放式居家睡眠空間或儲藏平台。位於房屋斜屋頂與最高樓層天花板間的密閉空間，則稱為「閣樓(內部空間)」。位在高樓層，佔房間全長或寬度的內部空間，則稱為「迴廊(上層空間)」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Grandes espaços no andar superior diretamente abaixo do telhado de edifícios comerciais ou armazéns, originalmente sem divisórias, mas frequentemente modificados para uso secundário.Também pode ser usado para dormir  ou como plataformas de armazenamento definidas perto de tetos ou telhados e aberto  com vista para uma sala de estar abaixo. Para espaços fechados sob telhados inclinados, entre o telhado e o teto do andar superior, especialmente em casas, use "sótãos (espaços internos)". Para espaços interiores substanciais no nível de um andar superior, geralmente estendendo-se por todo o comprimento ou largura dos cômodos, use "galerias (espaços no nível superior)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
